WorldStage Newsonlineâ€“ Total Nigeria Plc, a major oil marketing company in Nigeria has released its annual report for the year ended 31 December, 2020 with 30% decline in revenue to N204.721 billion from N292.177 billion in 2019. The result showed a 9% drop in profit for the year to N2.063 billion from N2.279 billion in 2019. The company has declared a dividend of N2.063 billion for the year compared with N2.278 billion in 2019. This translated to a dividend of N6.08 per 50 kobo share. Total Nigeria Plc was incorporated in 1956 and was listed on the Nigerian Stock Exchange in 1979. Our first petrol station was commissioned at Herbert Macaulay Street, Yaba, Lagos in 1956. It has over 575 service stations and 3 lubricants blending plants and operates 5 aviation storage facilities and other facilities spread across the country. Total S.A. which holds 62% of Total Nigeria Plc is a publicly-traded oil company with businesses in exploration and production, refining, marketing, trading and more recently, solar. It is also a major player in the chemicals sector.